Raystonn, you fail to take into account SoS aggro or else you would be correct.  If I let out 3-4 SoS on a mob chances are I'm going to get aggro.  I know (from practice) I can easily drop draughts as much as I want without worrying about aggro. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=evastoz>EvastoZ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/21/03 6:11:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25467.topic&index=42>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Strike of Solusek</span><hr size=1> One thing that some people have touched on that has not really been fully discussed is total mana efficient damage (our job).  What I mean is given a limited amount of mana (I know you can harvest, regen mana, mod rod, etc.), but let's just stick to a set mana pool for a moment... how much damage can you do in a given fight.  Now there are short exp grinding fight, longer mini-boss exp and loot fights and big bad boss mob fights.  Each could require a slightly different strategy.  But looking at the damage-to-mana ratio of a spell (and lets leave out crits since they are kinda hard to predict) then Sos is the best single target direct damage spell there is for the numbers (except the two Bane spells).  I know that you now need to take into consideration aggro and how long the mob takes to kill (well, and also is it resistant to fire attacks).<br>
I would like to know given the same AA skills (lets not compare a person with SCS3, SCM3, etc. to someone with no AA points at all).... what's the best way to conserve my lifeblood MANA, and yet do my job to the best of my abilities?<br>
It comes down to a routine.  Which is best for each kind of encounter.. small nukes with pausing, small nukes no pausing, small nukes with concusions, small and big nukes mixed, rain spells? (if they land rain spells have a great ratio)... you get the idea.  In each situation one of these is probably going to be the best approach. Figuring out which approach that is... well, that is the game we call EQ. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
